&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Analyst Intern&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Seeking a detail-oriented Business Analyst Intern to gather requirements, analyze processes, and deliver data-driven recommendations that improve business performance. The role partners with stakeholders, product owners, and technical teams to translate business needs into clear specifications and ensure successful delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Elicit, document, and validate business requirements with business stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support translation requirements into functional specifications, acceptance criteria, and test cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze business processes, identify gaps and improvement opportunities, and recommend solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create clear, persuasive PowerPoint presentations and decks for executives, stakeholders, and project teams; design visuals (charts, process flows, one-pagers) that convey findings and recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate communication between business stakeholders and development/QA teams; manage stakeholder expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and prioritize product/backlog items with product owners or project managers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce clear documentation: requirements, process flows, decision matrices, and status reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and ability to synthesize complex information into concise deliverables and presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prioritize competing requests and manage time effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Slide crafting skills: narrative flow, consistent branding, concise messaging, and effective data visualization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of software development lifecycle and testing principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with project management tools (Jira, Confluence, Trello) and version control for documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
